The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of random forests and feature engineering suggests that the paper may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of gradient magnitudes and locality-sensitive hashing may also suggest multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
